sion. *Shunt fraction measurement is made by the 100% oxygen method (see APPENDIX for details); if the suspicion for PAVM is especially high, contrast echocardiography or radionuclide scanning could be used as first-line tests rather than shunt fraction measurement. †Three-
dimensional CT imaging of the chest is a reasonable alternative to pulmonary angiography.

